# Component Patterns

## Naming Convention

Use `xo-` prefixed BEM: `xo-{block}__{element}--{modifier}`

Examples: `xo-product-card__header`, `xo-btn--primary`, `xo-price--larger`

Newer custom sections may use inline scoped `<style>` blocks with shorter BEM-ish classes (e.g. `t-chip`, `btn--ghost`), scoped by section ID: `#section-{{ section.id }} .class`.

## Web Components

All interactivity uses custom elements with `xo-` prefix and attribute-based config:

| Component | Element | Key Attributes |
|-----------|---------|---------------|
| Container | `<xo-container>` | — |
| Grid | `<xo-grid>` | `--lg`, `--md`, `--xs` column CSS vars |
| Carousel | `<xo-carousel>` | `xo-per-view`, `xo-per-move`, `xo-loop`, `xo-autoplay`, `xo-breakpoints` (JSON) |
| Modal | `<xo-modal>` + `<xo-modal-trigger>` | `xo-name` |
| Collapse | `<xo-collapse>` + `<xo-collapse-trigger>` | named instances |
| Tabs | `<xo-tabs>` + `<xo-tabs-trigger>` + `<xo-tabs-pane>` | `xo-name` |
| Tooltip | `<xo-tooltip>` | `xo-title`, `xo-placement` |
| Toast | `<xo-toast>` | type: `success` / `warning` / `error` |
| Animation | `<xo-animate>` + `<xo-animate-item>` | `xo-cascade`, `xo-duration`, `xo-order`, `xo-type` |
| Lazy image | `<xo-lazyload>` | `is: wc` attribute |
| Video | `<xo-video-custom>` / `<xo-video-cover>` | poster, autoplay |
| Product | `<xo-product>` | variant/product/section IDs |
| Cart add | `<xo-cart-add>` | disables when unavailable |
| Quantity | `<xo-cart-quantity>` + `<xo-cart-quantity-minus/plus>` | min/max/step |

IMPORTANT: Reuse these existing web components instead of writing new JavaScript. Only create new JS when no existing component covers the use case.

## Button System

Render via `{% render 'button' %}` snippet. Three style variants:

- **primary**: gold bg, dark text, pill-shaped (`--button-radius: 10rem`)
- **secondary**: transparent bg, dark text/border, pill-shaped
- **link**: text-only, no background

Parameters: `style`, `size`, `link`, `text`, `icon`, `icon_position`

Effects: `slide-up` (hover text animation), loading spinner. Icon support via `xo-btn__icon`.

Icon-only buttons: `{% render 'button-icon' %}` with sizes `sm`/`md`/`lg`, types `boxed`/`circle`, effects `fill`/`rotate`/`slide-up`.

## Section Structure

Every section MUST use `{% render 'section-attr' %}` for standardized padding and color scheme:

```liquid
<section {% render 'section-attr', section: section %}>
  <xo-container>
    ...content...
  </xo-container>
</section>
```

This outputs: `class="xo-section color-{{ scheme }}"` plus CSS vars `--pt_dt`, `--pb_dt`, `--pt_mb`, `--pb_mb`, `--bg-color`, `--bg-gradient`.

Sections MUST include a `{% schema %}` tag defining name, settings, blocks, and presets.

### Post-Write Validation (Mandatory)

IMPORTANT: After creating or modifying any section, block, or snippet, run `validate_theme` via the Shopify MCP server to verify:
- Valid Liquid syntax and object references
- Correct `{% schema %}` structure (valid `tag` values, setting types, block definitions)
- No hallucinated filters or undefined objects

When unsure about `{% schema %}` properties (e.g. valid `tag` values, setting types, block limits), use `search_docs_chunks` to look up official Shopify documentation **before** writing the file.

## Blocks

Theme blocks live in `/blocks/` as standalone `.liquid` files. They are reusable across multiple sections.

- Reusable cross-section blocks → `blocks/{name}.liquid` with `{% schema %}` and `{% doc %}` tags
- Section-specific blocks → defined within the section's `{% schema %}` tag
- IMPORTANT: Support `@app` blocks in sections where merchants benefit from app extensions (product pages, cart, featured collections)
- Don't make blocks too granular — group related settings (e.g. author + date + comments = one block)

```liquid
{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Section Name",
  "blocks": [
    { "type": "@theme" },
    { "type": "@app" }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
```

## Grid Usage

```liquid
<xo-grid style="--lg: 4; --md: 2; --xs: 1;">
  ...grid items...
</xo-grid>
```

Column vars: `--xl`, `--lg`, `--md`, `--xs`. Gap vars: `--grid-desktop-*-spacing`, `--grid-mobile-*-spacing`.

## Stack Layout

```liquid
<div class='xo-stack' style='--ai: center; --jc: space-between; --gap: 20; --dir: column'>
```

## Icons

Use `{% render 'icon', name: 'arrow-right', size: '2.4rem', color: 'currentColor' %}`.

116 inline SVG icons available via the central dispatcher `snippets/icon.liquid`. RTL auto-flips directional icons for Arabic/Farsi/Hebrew/Urdu.

IMPORTANT: Do not install icon packages or use icon fonts. All icons are inline SVG snippets. Add new icons as `snippets/icon-{name}.liquid` and register in `snippets/icon.liquid`.

## Images

Use `{% render 'image' %}` snippet for all images:

- Lazy loading via `<xo-lazyload>` with shimmer skeleton placeholder
- Eager loading for above-fold content: `loading="eager"` + `fetchpriority="high"`
- Aspect ratio via `--xo-ratio-percent` CSS variable
- Focal point via `--x-pos` / `--y-pos`
- Product images: `{% render 'product-image' %}` with hover secondary image swap

## Price

Use `{% render 'price' %}` for all pricing. Handles regular/sale price, compare-at, currency codes, and unit pricing. Modifier `xo-price--larger` for PDP.

## Accessibility (Shopify Required)

IMPORTANT: These are mandatory for Shopify theme compliance.

### Images and Media
- All images MUST include the `alt` attribute — use `image.alt` or pass an `alt` parameter
- Decorative images use `alt=""` and `tabindex="-1"`

### Forms
- Form inputs MUST have a unique `id` with a matching `<label for="...">` attribute
- Group related form fields with `<fieldset>` and `<legend>` where appropriate

### Color Contrast
- Text contrast: minimum 4.5:1 for body text, 3:1 for text larger than 18px
- Non-text elements (borders, icons): minimum 3:1 contrast ratio
- IMPORTANT: When using opacity-reduced text (`--font-body-color-opacity: 0.75`), verify the effective contrast still passes

### Interactive Elements
- Use `{% render 'visually-hidden' %}` for screen-reader-only text (e.g. price labels)
- Add `aria-label` on all icon-only buttons and interactive custom elements
- Add `role="button"` + `tabindex="0"` on clickable custom elements that aren't `<button>` or `<a>`
- Focus order must match DOM order (top-to-bottom, left-to-right)
- Visible focus indicator on all interactive elements — use `focus-inset` class

### Touch Targets
- Minimum touch target size: 24x24 CSS pixels for pointer inputs
- Ensure adequate spacing between adjacent interactive elements on mobile

### Semantic HTML
- Use semantic elements: `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, `<header>`, `<footer>`
- Headings h1–h6 must follow logical hierarchy (no skipping levels)
- Use `<button>` for actions, `<a>` for navigation — not the reverse

### Reduced Motion
- IMPORTANT: Wrap entrance animations with `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference)` or respect the user preference in JS
